'''''Chaos and Disorder,''''' released in 1996 by [[Prince (artist)|Prince]] (his stage name at that time being the unpronounceable symbol [[File:Prince logo.svg|12px]]), was his final album of new material for [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros]], and was therefore produced as a collection of leftovers only put on record to fulfill contractual obligations. Chaos and Disorder was one of Prince's least commercially successful releases and met mixed reviews upon release. Some reviewers <!-- Whom? Please cite if possible. -->commented that had it not been a Prince release, it would have been met with much wider approval. The album reached #26 in the US and #14 in the UK, and is now out of print.

'''''Chaos and Disorder,''''' released in 1996 by [[Prince (artist)|Prince]] (his stage name at that time being an unpronounceable symbol), was his final album of new material for [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros]], and was therefore produced as a collection of leftovers only put on record to fulfill contractual obligations. Chaos and Disorder was one of Prince's least commercially successful releases and met mixed reviews upon release. Some reviewers <!-- Whom? Please cite if possible. -->commented that had it not been a Prince release, it would have been met with much wider approval. The album reached #26 in the US and #14 in the UK, and is now out of print.
